==Finnish==

===Etymology===
Originally so-called weak suffixal gradation form of the partitive suffix ''[[-ta#Finnish|-ta]]'', /ða/ or /ðæ/.

===Case suffix===
'''-a''' (''in words with back vowel harmony'')

'''-ä''' (''in words with front vowel harmony'')

# Suffix for the [[partitive]] case.

====Usage====
This suffix is used after a short vowel or the plural marker ''-j-''.

