==Swedish==
===Adjectives===
The ending '''-a''' after an adjective (''absolute'') indicates that the corresponding noun is either in plural, ''or'' that it is definte form, sexus ''non-masculinum''


===Verbs===
The ending '''-a''' is very often used to create new [[verb]]s, tempus infinitive.

====Examples====
*[[Disk]] = ''[[Dishes]]''
*:Att disk'''a''' = ''To do the dishes''
*[[Lås]] = ''[[Lock]]''
*:Att lås'''a''' en dörr = ''To lock a door''



